VALUES
(43, 5, 40, 43, 1, 11, 11, 'that ye might have life', 'Rejection of Jesus by His Own', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection present in both passages. John 5:40 emphasizes the unwillingness to come to Jesus for life, while John 1:11 notes that His own did not receive Him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 40, 19, 81, 11, 11, NULL, 'Rejection of Divine Invitation', 'Both passages emphasize the refusal of the people to respond to God''s call. In John 5:40, the refusal to come to Jesus for life parallels the unwillingness of Israel to hearken to God''s voice in Psalms 81:11.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 40, 23, 49, 7, 7, 'ye will not come to me', 'Connection of Rejection and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of the servant by man, with John 5:40 highlighting the unwillingness to come to Jesus for life, while Isaiah 49:7 speaks of the despised servant of the Lord. This connection highlights the theme of rejection faced by those sent by God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 40, 23, 50, 2, 2, NULL, 'Call for Response to God', 'Both passages emphasize the lack of response to God''s call. In John 5:40, the refusal to come to Jesus contrasts with Isaiah 50:2''s lament over no one answering when called. This connection highlights the theme of divine invitation and human rejection.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 40, 40, 23, 37, 37, NULL, 'Rejection of Divine Invitation', 'Both passages emphasize the refusal to come to God for life and protection. In John 5:40, the refusal is to Jesus for life, while in Matthew 23:37, it reflects Jerusalem''s rejection of God''s desire to gather them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 40, 45, 6, 23, 23, 'that ye might have life', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between life and death. John 5:40 highlights the refusal to come to Jesus for life, while Romans 6:23 states that sin leads to death, but eternal life is a gift through Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 41, 43, 7, 18, 18, 'honour from men', 'Honor and Glory in John', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking glory. In John 5:41, Jesus states he does not seek honor from men, while John 7:18 contrasts this by emphasizing the importance of seeking the glory of the one who sent him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 41, 43, 5, 34, 34, 'I receive not honour from men', 'Honor and Testimony from Man', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of human validation. John 5:41 states, ''I receive not honour from men,'' while John 5:34 mentions, ''I receive not testimony from man,'' highlighting a similar theme of divine authority over human approval.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 41, 52, 2, 6, 6, 'honour from men', 'Honor and Glory from Men', 'This connection highlights the theme of not seeking honor or glory from men. Both passages emphasize a rejection of human approval in favor of a higher calling.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 41, 60, 2, 21, 21, 'I receive not honour from men', 'Honor and Suffering in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of honor in relation to suffering. John 5:41 emphasizes that Christ does not seek honor from men, while 1 Peter 2:21 encourages believers to follow Christ''s example of suffering, suggesting that true honor comes from enduring trials rather than seeking human approval.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 41, 61, 1, 17, 17, 'I receive not honour from men', 'Honor from God vs. Men', 'This connection highlights the contrast between receiving honor from men and receiving honor from God. While John 5:41 states that Jesus does not seek honor from men, 2 Peter 1:17 emphasizes the honor and glory bestowed upon Him by God the Father.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 43, 2, 25, 25, 'the love of God in you', 'Understanding Human Nature', 'Both passages emphasize the knowledge of what is in man. John 5:42 reveals a lack of divine love in people, while John 2:25 highlights Jesus'' understanding of human nature.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 62, 2, 15, 15, 'the love of God in you', 'Connection of Divine Love', 'This connection highlights the absence of divine love in both passages. John 5:42 states that the love of God is not present, while 1 John 2:15 warns against loving the world, implying that such love excludes the love of the Father.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 62, 3, 17, 17, 'the love of God in you', 'Love of God Connection', 'This connection highlights the absence of God''s love in those who lack compassion for others. Both passages emphasize that true love for God is demonstrated through caring for those in need.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 43, 8, 47, 47, 'the love of God in you', 'Connection of Divine Love and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between love for God and the ability to hear His words. The first verse indicates a lack of God''s love, while the second suggests that those not of God cannot hear His words.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 45, 8, 7, 7, 'the love of God in you', 'Love of God and Carnal Mind', 'This connection highlights the opposition between the love of God and the carnal mind. Both passages emphasize a lack of alignment with God''s nature, indicating enmity against Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 42, 16, 15, 15, 'love of God in you', 'Connection of Divine Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize God''s knowledge of human hearts. John 5:42 states that God knows the lack of love in individuals, while Luke 16:15 highlights that God knows the true intentions behind self-justification.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 42, 58, 4, 12, 13, 'the love of God in you', 'Connection of Divine Insight', 'Both passages emphasize the discernment of the heart. John 5:42 highlights the absence of God''s love, while Hebrews 4:12-13 speaks of the word of God revealing the thoughts and intents of the heart.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 43, 10, 25, 25, 'in my Father’s name', 'Connection of Authority in Names', 'Both passages emphasize coming in the Father’s name and the rejection of Jesus. They highlight the contrast between Jesus'' divine authority and the acceptance of others who come in their own name.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 40, 24, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of False Messiahs', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of individuals coming in the name of Christ, with John 5:43 highlighting rejection of the true messenger and Matthew 24:5 warning of deceivers claiming to be Christ. This connection highlights the contrast between true and false claims of messiahship.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 43, 17, 4, 6, 'in my Father’s name', 'Connection of Glorification and Name', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorification and the manifestation of the Father''s name. In John 5:43, Jesus speaks of coming in His Father''s name, while in John 17:6, He mentions manifesting the Father''s name to His followers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 58, 5, 4, 5, 'in my Father’s name', 'Connection of Divine Calling', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine calling and authority. In John 5:43, Jesus speaks of coming in His Father''s name, while Hebrews 5:4-5 emphasizes that Christ did not glorify Himself but was called by God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 40, 24, 24, 24, 'receive me not', 'Connection of False Messiahs', 'This connection highlights the theme of deception regarding messianic figures. Both passages emphasize the contrast between true and false representatives of God, with John 5:43 noting rejection of the true Christ and Matthew 24:24 warning of false Christs who will deceive many.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 44, 5, 36, 37, NULL, 'False Messiahs and Followers', 'This connection highlights the theme of individuals who rise up claiming authority and attract followers, only to ultimately fail. John 5:43 warns of those who come in their own name, while Acts 5:36-37 recounts historical figures who drew followers but were ultimately slain and dispersed.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 43, 44, 21, 38, 38, 'ye receive me not', 'Leadership and Reception of Figures', 'This connection highlights the theme of leadership and how figures are received by the people. In John 5:43, Jesus speaks of coming in His Father''s name and not being received, while Acts 21:38 refers to a leader who led men into the wilderness, suggesting a contrast in reception based on authority.', 'theme', 0.27899999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 44, 43, 12, 43, 43, 'seek not the honour that cometh from God only', 'Praise of Men vs. God', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between seeking honor from men and seeking honor from God. John 5:44 questions belief when one seeks honor from others, while John 12:43 states that some loved the praise of men more than God''s praise.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 44, 45, 2, 29, 29, 'honour that cometh from God only', 'Honor from God vs. Men', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between seeking honor from men and receiving praise from God. John 5:44 questions the belief of those who seek honor from one another, while Romans 2:29 highlights that true praise comes from God, not from men.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 44, 50, 2, 3, 3, 'honour one of another', 'Honor and Humility in Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking honor from God rather than from others. John 5:44 critiques seeking honor from one another, while Philippians 2:3 encourages humility and valuing others above oneself.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 44, 40, 23, 5, 5, 'seek not the honour that cometh from God only', 'Honor and Public Display', 'Both passages emphasize the pursuit of honor from others rather than from God. John 5:44 critiques those who seek honor from one another, while Matthew 23:5 describes actions done to be seen by men.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 44, 45, 8, 7, 8, 'seek not the honour that cometh from God only', 'Honor and the Carnal Mind', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking honor. Both passages emphasize the conflict between human recognition and divine approval, illustrating that those focused on earthly honor cannot align with God''s will.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
